⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Redemption
node CPS · CPS · ⟦The Redemption:CPS:073389⟧

WHO   — The Redemption — saved by being seen
WHAT  — The half of Dostoevsky the film keeps and lands: not escape from punishment but redemption through being known and loved by a witness.
WHERE — CPS · Crime + Punishment in Suburbia  Framework inputs: Crime + Punishment in Suburbia (2000)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the movie's real wager — the same as the novel's — is that what saves the guilty is not getting away with it, but being seen and loved anyway.
HOW   — By Vincent's steady, unjudging love and Roseanne's slow acceptance of being seen.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the half of the novel the screen can film: not the syllogism, but the salvation — a guilty girl, seen and loved, beginning to come back.

